{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774643213,"nonce":"LP1vEgZmZGGR+YHBZ5k3Fr5FTwY=","message":"Ambiguity clarification for comment #1 (Population-based adversary approach):\n\nThe comment references \"loss oscillation and weak SISU conditioning observed in single-adversary minimax training\" without specifying the model configuration. Based on issue 3b70482 comment #4, this refers to:\n\n- Architecture: GRU, 180 hidden units, additive SISU gating\n- Training: minimax adversarial with single GaussianBumpAdversary (3 Gaussian bumps)\n- Hyperparameters: force_max=2.0, n_adversary_steps=5, batch_size=250, controller_lr=1e-4, adversary_lr=3e-4\n- Training: 2000 warmup batches + 5000 adversarial batches\n- Task: center-out delayed reaches, constant length 0.5\n- Loss: running_cost, loss_update disabled (no adaptive control cost ratio)\n- 4 independent seeds\n\nThe \"loss oscillation\" refers to seed 2 showing adversary spike at batch 1000 (ctrl_loss 9.76 -\u003e 10.81), and the \"weak SISU conditioning\" refers to all seeds showing 0.00% SISU velocity effect at batch 1499.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}